 responsive to those critiques. While the so-called postmodern critique of metaphysics—which Brown problematizes as insufficiently critical of political ideology—is often read as a challenge to religion, Brown’s readings suggest that the deconstructive and Marxist critiques of metaphysics present an opportunity for the reemergence of a historical and politically engaged form of religion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical theology. 0aSocial justice. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Religion. 4aPolitics and Law : Marxism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849587340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438495873423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438495873/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles